I agree 100% with 'Guest'.<br /><br />What's the point of keeping an exact format if we're not going to keep it exact.  If we start omitting differences that (in the present) we feel are unimportant, we'll be repeatnig the whole iNES fiasco all over again.<br /><br />Plus things can change.  Despite the differences we see between MMC3 and MMC6 now, back in the day they didn't feel it important to distinguish between the two.  Are you really suggesting we take that same road?  That'll just cause more problems down the line.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Thu Jul 28, 2005 3:04 pm</p><hr />
